<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1907-11-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1907-11-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="336" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 9160/37.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Sands</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-11-13"><hi rend="italic">November 13,
                                    1907</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Sands reports that the negroes assaulted at Zacapa are still waiting
                            for department’s decision in the case before departing for the United
                            States. Says they are without funds and that they are living at his
                            expense. Mr. Sands asks for instructions.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>